      "side": 1,
      "message": "[🟡 Suggestion] Line 193: `_lastInvAspect` is updated immediately after requesting the new geometry, even if the compositor clamps or refuses the requested size. That makes the next frame with the same aspect ratio look unchanged, so the area-preserving correction may not be retried and the PiP can remain at an incorrect shape. Update the cached aspect only after the observed window size is within tolerance of the requested aspect, or leave it unchanged when the applied geometry does not match the request.\n\n```suggestion\nroot._setAspectGeometry(newWidth, newHeight);\nif (Math.abs(root.width - newWidth) \u003c\u003d 1 \u0026\u0026 Math.abs(root.height - newHeight) \u003c\u003d 1) {\n    _lastInvAspect \u003d r;\n    _lastInvAspectInit \u003d true;\n}\n```",
