      "side": 1,
      "message": "[🟡 Suggestion] Line 230: The aspect-adjustment guard is cleared immediately after assigning width/height, but the earlier comment notes that window property-change signals can be delivered asynchronously by the window manager. If those delayed signals arrive after `_adjustingAspect` is already false, programmatic changes can be misclassified as user resizes and invoke the opposite resize path, causing extra geometry changes/saves or feedback loops on some compositors. Keep the guard active until the event loop has processed the resulting geometry notifications, or use a pending-target/idempotent check for both width and height handlers.\n\n```suggestion\nfunction _setAspectGeometry(newWidth, newHeight) {\n    _adjustingAspect \u003d true;\n    if (newWidth !\u003d\u003d width)\n        width \u003d newWidth;\n    if (newHeight !\u003d\u003d height)\n        height \u003d newHeight;\n    Qt.callLater(() \u003d\u003e { _adjustingAspect \u003d false; });\n}\n```",
